Yes. Start with this architecture:

```text
Media files:
Blazor/MudBlazor + Uppy
    → Backend Tus endpoint
    → On-prem temp folder
    → FFmpeg convert to WAV
    → Upload WAV to Blob Storage
    → Queue message

Other files:
Blazor/MudBlazor + Uppy
    → Direct Blob upload using SAS / later Azure SDK
    → Queue message
```

Important: **Uppy + Tus does parallel uploads across files** using `limit`. Each file is uploaded resumably in chunks. For true parallel chunks inside the same file, Azure Blob block upload is better. Uppy Tus is excellent for resumable media uploads; Uppy’s Tus plugin supports reliable resumable uploads and has a configurable concurrency limit. ([Uppy][1])

